@ENDNODE
@NODE install "Installation"

Please use enclosed install-skript.

If you want to install by hand, then copy the catalog ("ChemicalDB.catalog") in the
directory "SYS:Locale/Catalogs/deutsch";
the program-file ("ChemicalDB"),
and this guide-file ("ChemicalDB.guide")
to a place you'd like.

Now you can use the program without an restriction.

@ENDNODE
@NODE start "Programmstart"

The program can be started by CLI (Shell) without following arguments.

But you can also doubleclick on the icon of the program.

@ENDNODE
@NODE using "Using ChemicalDB"

Using this program is the easiest thing in the world.
To every element ChemicalDB consists of a gadget. Just click on it and
the most important datas to every element were shown.

Within this window you can find some other gadgets.
Behind the point "Discoverer:" are gadgets of the people, who discovered the
choosen element.
By clicking on it, a window with the most important datas are shown.


The menuitem "Discoverer" shows a list with discoverer and the most important
datas to every discoverer.


The menuitem "Subatomic particles" shows a window with thw most important datas
to electrons, protons etc.


The menuitem "Create reactionformula" shows a window. Here you can create a
reactionsformula (also the wordformula).
But the second reactionelement must be one of them:

 - Bromine
 - Chlorine
 - Fluorine
 - Iodine
 - Carbon
 - Oxygen
 - Sulphur
 - Selenium
 - Hydrogen
 - Carbonate
 - Cyanide
 - Chlorate
 - Hydroxyde
 - Hydrogencarbonate
 - Nitrate
 - Nitrite
 - Phosphate
or
 - Sulfate

The first element can be choosen freely. Then you only have to choose the valenz of it.
You can also choose the same element 2 times.

@ENDNODE
